     becomes the last clause of the predicate concerned.

     _Meta-predicate_ with arguments: `assertz_fact(fact)'.



 -- PREDICATE: assertz_fact/2:
     `assertz_fact(Fact, Ref)'

     Same as `assertz_fact/1', instantiating `Ref' to a unique
