 -- PREDICATE: get_form_input/1:
     `get_form_input(Dict)'

     Translates input from the form (with either the POST or GET
     methods, and even with CONTENT_TYPE multipart/form-data) to a
     dictionary `Dict' of _attribute_=_value_ pairs. If the flag
     `raw_form_values' is `off' (which is the default state), it
     translates empty values (which indicate only the presence of an
     attribute) to the atom `'$empty'', values with more than one
     line (from text areas or files) to a list of lines as strings,
     the rest to atoms or numbers (using `name/2'). If the flag `on',
     it gives all values as atoms, without translations.



 -- PREDICATE: get_form_value/3:
